                    <h2 class="university-secation-heading mt-5">MBBS in Armenia for Indian Students</h2>
                    <p>MBBS in Armenia among Indian students has become extremely popular in the last ten years. Its low
                        cost, cultural closeness and streamlined admission system makes it a great substitute to
                        pursuing medicine in India or other developing nations such as Ukraine or Philippines.
                    </p>
                    <p>Through institutions such as Gladzor, students in India are exposed to quality education that
                        meets the global standards. Armenian graduates have the option to sit FMGE (India), USMLE (USA),
                        PLAB (UK) and other international licensing exams.</p>
